537
00:58:36,113 --> 00:58:38,542
The more I fought,
the more powerful he became.

538
00:58:39,383 --> 00:58:41,403
It was impressive, really.

539
00:58:42,219 --> 00:58:46,559
And my miracle...
Clu saw the ISOs as an imperfection.

540
00:58:47,724 --> 00:58:49,474
So he destroyed them.

541
00:58:52,896 --> 00:58:54,446
The Purge.

542
00:58:55,098 --> 00:58:58,668
-He killed them all?
-It was genocide.

543
00:58:59,703 --> 00:59:02,923
! tried to get back
but I couldn't get to the portal.

544
00:59:03,874 --> 00:59:07,823
It uses massive power
and it can't stay open forever.

545
00:59:09,112 --> 00:59:11,192
And like a safe, it..

546
00:59:11,515 --> 00:59:14,004
It can only be opened from the outside.

547
00:59:16,253 --> 00:59:18,773
It closed on me, Sam.

548
00:59:19,656 --> 00:59:21,796
That's why I never came home.

549
00:59:29,032 --> 00:59:30,992
So the portal, it activated

550
00:59:31,301 --> 00:59:33,790
when I came in. So it's open now.

551
00:59:34,171 --> 00:59:35,100
Not for long.

552
00:59:35,272 --> 00:59:37,612
Only one millicycle, about eight hours.

553
00:59:37,974 --> 00:59:40,994
So we go now. Go home.
We make a run for it.

554
00:59:41,445 --> 00:59:43,375
-We get you out of here.
-Don't rush.

555
00:59:43,680 --> 00:59:45,640
What do you mean?
The portal's gonna close.

556
00:59:48,051 --> 00:59:49,511
What? What is it?

557
00:59:49,753 --> 00:59:53,383
The moment Flynn is on the Grid, Clu
will stop at nothing to obtain his disk.

558
00:59:53,924 --> 00:59:55,794
My disk is everything, Sam.

559
00:59:56,093 --> 00:59:59,163
It's the master key. The golden ticket.
The way out.

560
01:00:00,664 --> 01:00:03,794
-And not just for me.
-What do you mean?

561
01:00:04,267 --> 01:00:06,696
Our worlds are more connected
than anyone knows.

562
01:00:07,070 --> 01:00:09,060
Clu figures if 1 can be in...

563
01:00:09,372 --> 01:00:10,892
He can be out?

564
01:00:11,141 --> 01:00:14,331
-With my disk, it's possible.
-And then what?

565
01:00:15,345 --> 01:00:16,924
Game over.

566
01:00:17,914 --> 01:00:20,434
The guy doesn't dig imperfection.

567
01:00:22,252 --> 01:00:24,471
What's more imperfect than our world?

568
01:00:26,289 --> 01:00:29,249
I can't let that happen. I won't.

569
01:00:30,060 --> 01:00:32,900
So what do we do? Nothing?

570
01:00:33,330 --> 01:00:35,960
It's amazing how productive
doing nothing can be.

571
01:00:36,366 --> 01:00:39,586
Clu's planning something.
We've known that for a while.

572
01:00:40,403 --> 01:00:41,633
Programs have been disappearing.

573
01:00:41,838 --> 01:00:44,208
There's unrest out there,
even revolution.

574
01:00:44,574 --> 01:00:48,324
If we sit tight, Clu might
be brought down from the inside.

575
01:00:48,879 --> 01:00:51,839
If the portal is closing, we can't
sit around. We have to move now.

576
01:00:52,282 --> 01:00:56,562
Tell me, what brought you here,
to the Grid?

577
01:00:57,621 --> 01:00:59,321
Alan got your page.

578
01:00:59,589 --> 01:01:02,049
I didn't send any page.

579
01:01:02,826 --> 01:01:03,966
It was Clu.

580
01:01:04,161 --> 01:01:06,741
Clu sent that page.
That's why you're here.

581
01:01:07,130 --> 01:01:09,790
This is all his design.
He wanted a new piece

582
01:01:10,200 --> 01:01:12,390
on the board to change the game!

583
01:01:12,736 --> 01:01:14,606
With you, he got more
than he ever dreamed.

584
01:01:14,905 --> 01:01:19,475
This is precisely what he wants.
Us together heading for the portal.

585
01:01:20,143 --> 01:01:23,833
It's his game now.
The only way to win is not to play.

586
01:01:26,316 --> 01:01:28,046
Well, that's a hell of a way to live.

587
01:01:28,318 --> 01:01:29,748
But it is a way.

588
01:01:34,691 --> 01:01:36,361
We can go home.

589
01:01:38,428 --> 01:01:40,178
Don't you want that?

590
01:01:41,031 --> 01:01:45,921
Sometimes life has a way of moving you
past things like wants and hopes.

591
01:01:47,270 --> 01:01:51,460
That's great, Dad.
Keep telling yourself that.

592
01:01:57,647 --> 01:01:58,727
Good night, Sam.

593
01:02:22,072 --> 01:02:24,152
How can he be so afraid
of his own creation?

594
01:02:24,474 --> 01:02:27,314
I mean, he built Clu.
Why doesn't he just end him?

595
01:02:28,945 --> 01:02:30,815
He could,
but it would require reintegration.

596
01:02:31,114 --> 01:02:32,454
Yeah, all right.

597
01:02:32,682 --> 01:02:35,962
Flynn would never survive the event.
It would mean the end of them both.

598
01:02:37,587 --> 01:02:39,837
If he refuses to save himself, then I will.

599
01:02:44,294 --> 01:02:45,814
How?

600
01:02:46,062 --> 01:02:48,281
I'm going through the portal.

601
01:02:48,632 --> 01:02:50,212
Clu wants Flynn's disk, not mine.

602
01:02:50,467 --> 01:02:54,567
I'm going to find Alan and we'll figure
this thing out from the other side.

603
01:02:55,171 --> 01:02:58,241
This may be Clu's game here, but
in my world, he's gone in one keystroke.

604
01:02:58,708 --> 01:03:01,638
But I can't do anything
unless I get to the portal.

605
01:03:03,380 --> 01:03:04,370
And my guts tell me

606
01:03:04,547 --> 01:03:08,147
that you don't want to be stuck
in this place for eternity either.

607
01:03:10,787 --> 01:03:14,156
I really think you should consider
your father's wisdom.

608
01:03:15,458 --> 01:03:17,068
Il have.

609
01:04:20,890 --> 01:04:22,620
There's someone I once knew,

610
01:04:22,892 --> 01:04:25,672
a program named Zuse
who fought alongside the ISOs.

611
01:04:26,096 --> 01:04:29,026
They say he can get anyone anywhere.

612
01:04:31,101 --> 01:04:32,881
How do I find him?

613
01:04:36,039 --> 01:04:37,709
This is his sector.

614
01:04:41,211 --> 01:04:43,901
Make it there alive, and he'll find you.

615
01:05:24,954 --> 01:05:26,414
Sam?

616
01:05:30,160 --> 01:05:31,330
Sam?

617
01:06:03,593 --> 01:06:07,073
All programs are required
to present identity disks

618
01:06:07,630 --> 01:06:08,940
at city checkpoints.

619
01:06:13,403 --> 01:06:15,683
Hey, man. It's your lucky day.

620
01:06:22,879 --> 01:06:25,659
-Any program without their disk...
-Stop him!

621
01:06:26,082 --> 01:06:28,221
...Will be taken into custody.

622
01:06:30,153 --> 01:06:34,513
Any program in violation of their
function is subject to termination.

623
01:06:35,625 --> 01:06:38,695
Sam Flynn? You remember me?

624
01:06:39,429 --> 01:06:42,939
-Yeah. You gave me some advice.
-And you followed it.

625
01:06:44,834 --> 01:06:47,203
It's unfortunate we met the way we did.

626
01:06:48,805 --> 01:06:50,035
You have a good night.

627
01:06:50,240 --> 01:06:52,490
You're looking for someone.

628
01:06:55,378 --> 01:06:57,158
What makes you say that?

629
01:06:58,248 --> 01:07:00,028
Intuition.

630
01:07:02,252 --> 01:07:06,032
Sir, the sentries downtown
have recovered Flynn's light cycle.

631
01:07:07,824 --> 01:07:10,784
We've traced it to its point of origin.

632
01:07:36,085 --> 01:07:38,695
Prepare the light runner, Quorra.

633
01:07:39,689 --> 01:07:41,969
We're going downtown.

634
01:08:04,614 --> 01:08:06,194
Thank you for bringing my son to me.

635
01:08:06,449 --> 01:08:07,589
Flynn!

636
01:08:07,784 --> 01:08:10,414
You don't need to go.
I've sent him to someone we can trust.

637
01:08:10,820 --> 01:08:12,720
Quorra, there is no choice.

638
01:08:13,856 --> 01:08:15,786
I won't lose him again.

639
01:08:17,993 --> 01:08:20,863
Chaos. Good news.

640
01:09:02,404 --> 01:09:04,894
Relax. They're occupied.

641
01:09:11,881 --> 01:09:15,191
His name is Castor. If you want to speak
to Zuse, you need to go through him.

642
01:09:15,685 --> 01:09:18,055
Where's your sense of humor,
my friend?

643
01:09:18,421 --> 01:09:21,381
Programs are disappearing.
Soon none of us will be left.

644
01:09:21,823 --> 01:09:24,254
Zuse can unite the factions,
foment revolution.

645
01:09:24,627 --> 01:09:27,697
-Of course Zuse can do these things.
-Grant me an audience.

646
01:09:28,163 --> 01:09:31,033
Your enthusiasm is intoxicating,
my dear Bartik,

647
01:09:31,466 --> 01:09:33,897
but Zuse's time is precious.

648
01:09:34,270 --> 01:09:36,350
We shall see.

649
01:09:38,207 --> 01:09:40,107
l brought your boy Flynn.

650
01:09:40,410 --> 01:09:44,889
If you'll excuse me for a moment,
l have to attend to something.

651
01:09:45,548 --> 01:09:48,447
But have a drink,
courtesy of the End of Line Club!

652
01:09:49,519 --> 01:09:50,659
It is happening.

653
01:09:50,853 --> 01:09:53,693
Come, away from
these primitive functions.

654
01:09:55,258 --> 01:09:57,338
The son of Flynn.

655
01:09:57,660 --> 01:10:02,050
Of all the innumerable possibilities,
he has to walk into mine.

656
01:10:03,533 --> 01:10:04,873
Libations

657
01:10:05,101 --> 01:10:07,651
for everybody!

658
01:10:10,573 --> 01:10:13,703
I'm Castor, your host.

659
01:10:14,177 --> 01:10:16,456
Provider of any and all entertainments

660
01:10:16,813 --> 01:10:19,123
and diversions.

661
01:10:19,482 --> 01:10:20,682
At your service.

662
01:10:23,319 --> 01:10:25,489
I'm looking for Zuse.

663
01:10:25,822 --> 01:10:28,402
Indeed. Many are.

664
01:10:28,791 --> 01:10:30,541
Where can I find him?

665
01:10:30,827 --> 01:10:34,367
This, pretty miss, is a conversation
best had behind closed doors.

666
01:10:34,897 --> 01:10:37,997
Perhaps we should retire
to my private lounge.

667
01:10:41,070 --> 01:10:44,059
I designed it myself, you know. It's true.

668
01:10:44,507 --> 01:10:48,427
I'm stepping away for a moment, boys.
Change the scheme, alter the mood.

669
01:10:49,011 --> 01:10:53,261
Electrify the boys and girls
if you'd be so kind.

670
01:10:56,352 --> 01:10:57,642
Thank you.

671
01:10:57,854 --> 01:11:00,374
Gem. My name is Gem.

672
01:11:42,165 --> 01:11:43,715
Cozy.

673
01:13:04,513 --> 01:13:07,003
-You are Clu.
-lam Clu.

674
01:13:07,383 --> 01:13:11,633
-You will create the perfect system.
-I will create the perfect system.

675
01:13:15,691 --> 01:13:18,411
Together we're gonna
change the world, man.

676
01:13:46,188 --> 01:13:47,148
Let's move.

677
01:13:49,292 --> 01:13:50,722
Zuse has been around

678
01:13:50,960 --> 01:13:52,710
since the earliest days
of the gaming grid.

679
01:13:53,362 --> 01:13:57,022
By necessity,
he has to mind all the percentages.

680
01:13:57,566 --> 01:13:59,295
All the angles.

681
01:13:59,568 --> 01:14:01,238
So when do I meet him?

682
01:14:04,040 --> 01:14:07,060
You just did.

683
01:14:10,813 --> 01:14:14,273
After the Purge,
I needed to reinvent myself.

684
01:14:14,784 --> 01:14:16,804
Self-preservation, you understand.

685
01:14:22,091 --> 01:14:26,161
Now, what can I do for you?

686
01:14:29,432 --> 01:14:31,242
I need to get to the portal.

687
01:14:31,534 --> 01:14:32,874
Well, it's closing quickly,

688
01:14:33,102 --> 01:14:35,472
as I'm sure you're aware.

689
01:14:35,838 --> 01:14:37,208
Tick-tock, tick-tock.

690
01:14:37,440 --> 01:14:39,460
And it's quite the journey.

691
01:14:39,775 --> 01:14:42,264
Beyond the far reaches of the Outlands.

692
01:14:42,645 --> 01:14:46,655
Your father didn't want any programs
slipping out accidentally, did he?

693
01:14:48,551 --> 01:14:52,591
-Can you help me?
-Of course.

694
01:14:53,189 --> 01:14:56,499
But first, as a man who prides himself
on staying well informed,

695
01:14:56,993 --> 01:14:59,243
I must ask who sent you my way.

696
01:15:02,465 --> 01:15:04,425
Her name's Quorra.

697
01:15:04,734 --> 01:15:06,604
Said she met you a long time ago.

698
01:15:07,603 --> 01:15:09,743
Indeed she did.

699
01:15:10,072 --> 01:15:11,652
Many cycles ago.

700
01:15:12,842 --> 01:15:15,302
It was a different time.

701
01:15:15,678 --> 01:15:19,138
But we're not here to relive the past.
Let's see about your future, shall we?

702
01:15:19,648 --> 01:15:21,988
We'll have to change your attire

703
01:15:22,351 --> 01:15:25,281
and you'll need a forged disk.
Not easy these days.

704
01:15:25,721 --> 01:15:27,300
And of course you'll need transport

705
01:15:28,524 --> 01:15:31,214
to cross the Sea of Simulation.

706
01:15:42,705 --> 01:15:45,045
This is going to be quite the ride.

707
01:15:57,853 --> 01:15:59,463
I believed in users once before.

708
01:16:01,490 --> 01:16:03,070
Playing all the angles.

709
01:16:07,763 --> 01:16:08,933
Resist!

710
01:16:17,840 --> 01:16:21,150
The game has changed, son of Flynn!

711
01:16:37,893 --> 01:16:40,083
I met your friend. He's fantastic!

712
01:16:40,429 --> 01:16:43,469
Behold! The son of our maker!

713
01:16:57,646 --> 01:16:58,906
Yeah!

714
01:17:08,924 --> 01:17:10,154
Yeah, yeah!

715
01:17:12,161 --> 01:17:13,301
Yeah, yeah!

716
01:17:49,798 --> 01:17:51,258
Go, go!

717
01:17:56,805 --> 01:17:58,675
Let's split, man.

718
01:18:38,847 --> 01:18:40,657
A little help here maybe?

719
01:19:02,204 --> 01:19:03,374
Your disk.

720
01:19:04,473 --> 01:19:05,463
Dad, it's gone.

721
01:19:06,642 --> 01:19:07,751
It is.

722
01:19:10,646 --> 01:19:12,135
I'm sorry. I know I messed up.

723
01:19:14,483 --> 01:19:15,413
We can go back.

724
01:19:15,584 --> 01:19:18,014
-l can go back.
-No, we stay together.

725
01:19:18,387 --> 01:19:21,076
-Dad, I can do this.
-You've done enough already!

726
01:19:26,729 --> 01:19:28,539
Sam, you're really...

727
01:19:31,467 --> 01:19:33,487
You're messing with my Zen thing, man.

728
01:19:36,305 --> 01:19:37,535
She's stable.

729
01:19:38,807 --> 01:19:41,737
-So what do we do now?
- don't know. Nothing.

730
01:19:43,078 --> 01:19:44,828
We do nothing.

731
01:19:45,614 --> 01:19:46,983
Be still.

732
01:19:49,752 --> 01:19:51,212
Wait.

733
01:19:59,128 --> 01:20:01,678
You ever jump a freight train?

734
01:20:04,266 --> 01:20:07,106
We do it your way.
Full-on sprint to the portal.

735
01:20:07,536 --> 01:20:09,236
If we beat Clu there, we have a chance.

736
01:20:09,505 --> 01:20:10,705
Let's get her out of here.

737
01:20:29,758 --> 01:20:31,338
This'll take us there.

738
01:20:58,420 --> 01:21:00,640
-ls she gonna make it?
-I don't know.

739
01:21:00,989 --> 01:21:03,358
I've got to identify the damaged code.

740
01:21:03,726 --> 01:21:06,885
The sequencing
is just enormously complex.

741
01:21:08,397 --> 01:21:12,557
-But didn't you write it?
-Some of it. The rest of it is just

742
01:21:15,938 --> 01:21:18,218
beyond me.

743
01:21:19,742 --> 01:21:21,852
She's an ISO.

744
01:21:22,177 --> 01:21:24,347
Yeah. The last ISO.

745
01:21:26,915 --> 01:21:28,175
All this time,

746
01:21:28,384 --> 01:21:30,494
you were just protecting her.

747
01:21:30,819 --> 01:21:34,389
She's the miracle, man.
Everything I ever worked for.

748
01:21:36,225 --> 01:21:40,005
"A digital frontier
to reshape the human condition."

749
01:21:40,562 --> 01:21:43,432
l always thought
that was just a plug line.

750
01:21:43,866 --> 01:21:47,616
In our world,
she could change everything.

751
01:21:49,505 --> 01:21:51,405
Yeah.

752
01:21:54,343 --> 01:21:55,683
Check that out.

753
01:22:03,986 --> 01:22:05,885
She risked herself for me.

754
01:22:08,056 --> 01:22:10,135
Some things are worth the risk.

755
01:22:23,972 --> 01:22:25,701
Look at this.

756
01:22:28,777 --> 01:22:31,967
Now, that is impressive
if ldo say so myself.

757
01:22:33,816 --> 01:22:36,656
Come on, it's gonna take a while
for her system to reboot.

758
01:22:37,085 --> 01:22:39,925
Now it's time for you to tell me a story.

759
01:22:58,440 --> 01:23:00,490
The boy and Flynn are gone.

760
01:23:00,809 --> 01:23:04,209
I presume, Your Excellency,
they perished in the elevator.

761
01:23:08,116 --> 01:23:09,516
You presume?

762
01:23:11,820 --> 01:23:13,780
Find them.

763
01:23:18,327 --> 01:23:21,317
Icecaps are melting,
war in the Middle East,

764
01:23:21,763 --> 01:23:23,693
Lakers‘Celtics back at it.

765
01:23:25,067 --> 01:23:27,907
I don't know. Rich are getting richer,
poor are getting poorer.

766
01:23:28,337 --> 01:23:30,767
Cell phones, online dating, Wi-Fi.

767
01:23:31,139 --> 01:23:33,889
-What's Wi-Fi?
-Wireless interlinking.

768
01:23:34,309 --> 01:23:36,859
-Of digital devices?
-Yeah.

769
01:23:38,447 --> 01:23:40,617
l thought of that in '85.

770
01:23:45,320 --> 01:23:47,219
Mom and Dad are...

771
01:23:49,191 --> 01:23:51,181
-l assume that...
-Yeah.

772
01:23:54,696 --> 01:23:56,806
Mac when I was 12

773
01:23:57,132 --> 01:23:59,741
and Gram five years later.

774
01:24:02,838 --> 01:24:06,268
You remember that night
when you didn't come home?

775
01:24:06,775 --> 01:24:07,884
-Well...
-You said...

776
01:24:08,076 --> 01:24:09,946
I said I'd show you the Grid.

777
01:24:12,214 --> 01:24:14,294
You should have seen this place
back then.

778
01:24:15,484 --> 01:24:20,204
I couldn't wait to show it to you.
Could not wait.

779
01:24:20,889 --> 01:24:23,139
Must have been something
before Clu screwed it up.

780
01:24:23,492 --> 01:24:25,042
No, no, he...

781
01:24:26,995 --> 01:24:29,394
He's me. I screwed it up.

782
01:24:31,166 --> 01:24:33,066
Chasing after perfection.

783
01:24:35,370 --> 01:24:38,650
Chasing after
what was right in front of me.

784
01:24:39,641 --> 01:24:41,370
Right in front of me.

785
01:24:43,445 --> 01:24:45,554
Look what you've accomplished.

786
01:24:46,181 --> 01:24:47,790
It's incredible.

787
01:24:48,050 --> 01:24:49,310
Sam,

788
01:24:50,385 --> 01:24:53,315
I'd have given it all up
for one more day with you.

789
01:25:06,802 --> 01:25:07,732
Hey.

790
01:25:08,437 --> 01:25:10,397
Remember your old Ducati?

791
01:25:10,806 --> 01:25:13,646
You kidding? Not a day goes by
I don't think about that bike.

792
01:25:14,109 --> 01:25:17,619
-Yeah, well, I'm fixing her up.
-You busted my bike?

793
